label: Kanjur 'Bum Cha
description: The volume contains the teachings on the Perfection of Wisdom in 100,000 verses. The volume is written on cream coloured traditional Bhutanese paper made from dahpne bark. It is written in black ink. The text is wrapped in several layers of cloth and bound between two thick wood covers. The leaves are roughly 70x19.5cm. The opening folio is illuminated with drawings of Buddha and other decorative motifs. The first folios of the kanjur series have a deep blue or red background, most likely painted using malachite or lac. The text starts on the verso of the first folio, which also has a silk cover. 1 volume containing 364 folios of manuscripts on paper in loose leaf poti format. Dates of original material: unknown. Volume: Cha. Script(s) of material: Tibetan dBu can script.
